EDISON FIXTURE COMPANY, INCORPORATED, PLAINTIFF-APPELLANT, v. LOUIS TOLCHIN AND SHAENKIN, TRADING, ETC., DEFENDANT-APPELLEE. Argued October 8, 1924 Decided February 5, 1925.

Before Justices Teenchard, Minturn and Lloyd.

For the appellant, Herman B. J. Weclcstein. For the appellee, Thomas P. Gurley. Per Curiam.

This case was argued with, and is controlled by, out' decision in Edison Fixture Co., Inc., v. Copoulos, No. 475, of the'present term.

The judgment will be reversed and a venire de novo awarded.
